"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(min-width: 590px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSightcropped-e55b1d6-e1614184322814.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=555%2C370, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSightcropped-e55b1d6-e1614184322814.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1111%2C740 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSightcropped-e55b1d6-e1614184322814.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1668%2C1111 3x\" type=\"image/webp\"><source media=\"(min-width: 590px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSightcropped-e55b1d6-e1614184322814.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=555%2C370, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSightcropped-e55b1d6-e1614184322814.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1111%2C740 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSightcropped-e55b1d6-e1614184322814.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1668%2C1111 3x\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><img class=\"wp-image-620737 align size-landscape_thumbnail image-handler__image image-handler__image--aspect no-wrap js-lazyload\" data-src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSightcropped-e55b1d6-e1614184322814.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=620%2C413\" width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Two men sitting behind table with Edinburgh castle in the background\" title=\"HindSight\"></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></source></picture></div><div class=\"caption-hold\"><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\"><span class=\"caption-copy\"><i class=\"icon-arrow icon-camera-circle\"></i> HindSight was founded by Alex Macdonald (left), with design input coming from Team GB rider Callum Skinner (right).</span></figcaption><span class=\"im-image-caption\"> <i>HindSight</i></span></div>\n<p>HindSight was founded by physicist Alex Macdonald and the sunglasses were developed with input from Team GB Olympic track cyclist Callum Skinner.</p>\n<p>HindSight says its glasses make cyclists safer by allowing them “to see forwards and backwards with a simple shift of focus rather than having to turn their heads”.</p>\n<p>The glasses are intended to be a “stylish and functional” alternative to rear-view radars such as <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/first-look-friday/albion-cycling-kit/\">Garmin’s Varia</a> and conventional helmet- or bike-mounted mirrors.</p>\n<p>While road safety was seemingly the priority, HindSight says the concept offers an advantage to pro riders and other athletes, such as rowers, who might benefit from seeing competitors behind them, without having to look backwards.</p>\n<div class=\"image-handler__container image-handler__container--aspect\" style=\"padding-bottom: calc(100% / 1.501210653753);\">\n    <picture><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSight-Edge-Sport-10-b79e43c.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=298%2C199, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSight-Edge-Sport-10-b79e43c.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=598%2C399 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSight-Edge-Sport-10-b79e43c.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=898%2C599 3x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSight-Edge-Sport-10-b79e43c.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1198%2C799 4x\" type=\"image/webp\"><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSight-Edge-Sport-10-b79e43c.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=298%2C199, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/HindSight-Edge-Sport-10-b79e43c.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=598%2C399 2x, https://images.immediate.co.